<p>The fixed end-cap section is fitted with a <strong>Leybold 340M
turbomolecular pump</strong> and a <strong>Leybold CoolPower 130 cold
head</strong>, along with <strong>multiple electrical-vacuum
feedthroughs</strong>, vacuum gauges and a <strong>residual gas
analyser</strong>.  Concentric tripods, comprising low thermal
conductivity struts, centre and support three concentric aluminium
interface plates (Fig&#160;1 and Fig&#160;2). The middle annular and
the central circular interface plates are connected to the first and
second stages of the cold head via flexible copper cooling straps. An
outer annular interface plate completes the COC's 'optical bench
assembly' with multiple tapped holes providing a convenienet and
versatile method of mounting test equipment to the 15&#160;K (circular
inner), 70&#160;K (annular middle) and room temperature (annular
outer) temperature zones of the assembly.</p>

<p>The flexible cooling straps minimise, but do not totally eliminate,
the mechanical vibrations exported from the cold head and accommodate
dimensional changes during cool-down. The three temperature controlled
interface plates are supported at approximately the same height above
floor level as optical benches on an adjacent optical table and on
which may be mounted test and calibration equipment (Fig&#160;3).
</p> <TABLE
